# Three DataFrame types — keep them straight

## The axis everything here turns on

- **pandas** (`pandas.DataFrame`) — **driver memory only** — final-mile, plotting, fixtures
- **Pandas-on-Spark** (`pyspark.pandas.DataFrame`) — **distributed** — pandas syntax at Spark scale
- **Spark** (`pyspark.sql.DataFrame`) — **distributed** — native API, best performance, most features

## The key relationship

- Only the first lives on the driver; the other two are distributed on the **same engine**
- Pandas-on-Spark = a Spark DataFrame **+ a pandas-style index**
- That index is the source of this module's **gotchas**
